cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with facial landmarking, which is a computer vision problem related to image analysis and processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method that uses cascaded-regression-based methods and a gating mechanism to address appearance variability caused by significant pose variations. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on several popular datasets of 3D face images, which indicates that it may also belong to the category of graphics (cs.GR).
